{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e1757f3c-20fa-432f-8a18-f97a53f0fd67","content":"Here's a quick overview:\n\n**Templates:**\n- **ASP.NET Core Web API** (`dotnet new webapi`) — most popular for .NET\n- **Express.js** (`express-generator`) — Node.js\n- **FastAPI** / **Django REST Framework** — Python\n- **Spring Boot** — Java\n\n**Common Authentication Options (ASP.NET Core example):**\n| Option | Flag / Setup |\n|---|---|\n| JWT Bearer | `--auth None` + manual JWT config |\n| Individual Accounts (Identity) | `--auth Individual` |\n| Azure AD / Entra ID | `--auth SingleOrg` |\n| Azure AD B2C | `--auth IndividualB2C` |\n| Windows Auth | `--auth Windows` |\n\n**Quick start example (.NET):**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -n MyApi\n```\n\nWould you like help scaffolding a specific project with one of these options?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f9586f33-2f64-447c-bf65-3c72f9912982","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - it's a straightforward informational question I can answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":276},"id":"9c7c6113-3efe-45ac-a21f-42829e4feeff","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:51:51.466Z","parentId":"02f8cede-0aa9-463d-9cba-05720a7456bb"}
